title: Clashes in Iran as thousands gather at Mahsa Amini's grave, 40 days after her death
description: Clashes broke out throughout Iran Wednesday as thousands of people came to the burial site of Mahsa Amini in Saqqez, a city in the Kurdistan province, to mark 40 days since her death, semi-official Iranian state news agency ISNA said.

title: US imposes new sanctions on Iranian officials over crackdown on protests
description: The United States on Wednesday imposed a slew of new sanctions against Iranian officials involved in the ongoing crackdown on nationwide protests in Iran -- the latest US response to Tehran's efforts to quash outrage after the death of 22-year-old Mahsa Amini.

title: Xi Jinping just became unassailable. Here's why investors are running scared
description: When Chinese leader Xi Jinping secured a historic third term in power at the weekend and stacked his top team with loyalists in a clean sweep not seen since the Mao era, investors were quick to pass judgment.

title: Opinion: What three generations think of Britain's first non-White prime minister
description: Rishi Sunak becoming Prime Minister is an important moment of social history in Britain, yet it is a curiously understated one in some ways.

title: NASA announces team of scientists who will study mysterious 'UFO' events in the sky
description: The team will gather data on "events in the sky that cannot be identified as aircraft or known natural phenomena — from a scientific perspective," NASA officials said. The space agency selected 16 scientists and experts to join the group.
